Spanish Stocks: Banco Bilbao, Catalana, Iberdrola, Telefonica

-- B y   C h a r l e s   P e n t y
-- 
2011-03-21T12:27:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-21/spanish-stocks-banco-bilbao-catalana-iberdrola-telefonica.html
  Spain ’s IBEX 35 index rose,
climbing 191.50, or 1.9 percent, to 10,519.90 at 1.01 p.m. in
Madrid. The Madrid Stock Exchange General Index gained 1.7
percent today.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Spanish market. Symbols are in parentheses after company names.    Banco Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria SA (BBVA)   climbed 1.7
percent to 8.727 euros. The bank is selling four-year covered
bonds, according to two people with knowledge of the sale.    Banco Espanol de Credito SA (BTO)  , the lender controlled
by Banco Santander SA, rose 1.3 percent to 6.599 euros. The bank
plans to sell 600 million euros of four-year covered bonds,
according to a banker involved in the transaction.    Ferrovial SA (FER)   rose 1.6 percent to 8.77 euros.
Budimex SA, Poland’s largest builder and a unit of Ferrovial,
proposed paying its entire 2010 net income as a dividend.  Grupo Catalana Occidente SA (GCO SM) jumped 2.9 percent to
15.35 euros. The insurer was rated new “overweight” at
JPMorgan Chase & Co. with a price estimate of 18.10 euros.    Iberdrola SA (IBE)   climbed 2.3 percent to 5.96 euros. CA
Cheuvreux SA initiated coverage of the power company with an
“outperform” recommendation.    Telefonica SA (TEF)   climbed 2.2 percent to 17.675 euros.
The phone company was included by JPMorgan Chase & Co. on a list
of European stocks that offer value.  To contact the reporters on this story:
